## ⚠️ COMMON MISTAKES TO AVOID

### **❌ Mistake 1: Using std::cout**
```cpp
// Wrong
std::cout << "Error: " << error << std::endl;

// Right
Logger::error("Error: {}", error);
```

### **❌ Mistake 2: Using exceptions**
```cpp
// Wrong
throw std::runtime_error("Failed");

// Right
return std::unexpected(Error::Failed);
```

### **❌ Mistake 3: Raw pointers**
```cpp
// Wrong
Logger* logger = new Logger();
delete logger;

// Right
auto logger = std::make_unique<Logger>();
```

### **❌ Mistake 4: Using Qt**
```cpp
// Wrong — no Qt in RawrXD
#include <QString>
std::vector<QString> mixed;

// Right
#include "StdReplacements.hpp"
std::vector<std::string> coreData;
WideString uiString = WideString::fromStdString(coreData[0]);
```

### **❌ Mistake 5: Sync I/O**
```cpp
// Wrong — blocking UI
CreateProcess(...);
WaitForSingleObject(pi.hProcess, INFINITE);

// Right — async: use overlapped I/O, completion ports, or fire-and-forget with callbacks
```

